### DigitalKaam API Tests
### Run `npm run dev` in /backend before using these.
### In VS Code install the "REST Client" extension to run requests inline.
###
### WORKFLOW:
###   1. Run "Login" — copy access_token into @token below
###   2. All /api/chat and /api/booking routes require Authorization header
###   3. Replace <placeholder> values with real UUIDs from your DB

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:3000/api

# ── Paste your access_token here after login ──────────────────────────────────
@token = YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

# ── Paste real IDs here for booking/provider tests ────────────────────────────
@providerId   = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@bookingId    = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@disputeId    = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@sessionId    = session-test-001

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### HEALTH
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Health check
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/health

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Login — copy access_token into @token above
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user1@digitalkaam.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###

### Refresh access token (call when access_token expires)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### CHAT  (all routes require Authorization)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Send a message to the AI orchestrator
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}",
  "message": "Mujhe Malir mein AC repair chahiye kal subah"
}

###

### Follow-up message (same session)
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}",
  "message": "theek hai confirm kar do"
}

###

### Get full message history for a session
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/history?sessionId={{sessionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get all past sessions for the logged-in user
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### PROVIDERS  (public read, no auth required)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### List all active providers
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider

###

### Filter by service type
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider?serviceType=Electrician

###

### Filter by service type + area
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider?serviceType=AC%20Technician&area=Malir

###

### Get a single provider profile (includes reputation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider/{{providerId}}

###

### Get a provider's availability slots
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider/{{providerId}}/availability

###

### Get a provider's availability for a specific date
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider/{{providerId}}/availability?date=2026-05-20

###

### Get agent trace logs for a provider
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider/{{providerId}}/traces

###

### Get all traces for a session
GET {{baseUrl}}/provider/traces/{{sessionId}}

###

### Create a provider (admin/seed use)
POST {{baseUrl}}/provider
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test AC Technician",
  "phone": "0300-1234567",
  "email": "ac@digitalkaam.pk",
  "service_type": "AC Technician",
  "specialization": "AC Repair & Gas Refill",
  "experience_years": 6,
  "hourly_rate": 900,
  "capacity": 4,
  "travel_radius": 15,
  "area": "Malir",
  "lat": 24.8957,
  "lng": 67.1958,
  "rating": 4.5,
  "review_count": 12,
  "reliability_score": 88,
  "status": "active"
}

###

### Update a provider
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/provider/{{providerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "hourly_rate": 1000,
  "status": "active"
}

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AVAILABILITY
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get availability (all providers or filter by provider + date)
GET {{baseUrl}}/availability?providerId={{providerId}}&date=2026-05-20

###

### Create an availability slot
POST {{baseUrl}}/availability
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "provider_id": "{{providerId}}",
  "date": "2026-05-20",
  "start_time": "10:00",
  "end_time": "12:00",
  "is_booked": false,
  "travel_buffer": 30
}

###

### Mark a slot as booked
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/availability/<slot-id>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "is_booked": true
}

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### BOOKINGS  (all routes require Authorization)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get the logged-in user's bookings  ← CHANGED from /user/:userId
GET {{baseUrl}}/booking/user/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get a single booking (with provider info)
GET {{baseUrl}}/booking/{{bookingId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update booking lifecycle status  (provider calls this)
### Valid statuses: confirmed → en_route → arrived → in_progress → completed → feedback_pending
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/booking/{{bookingId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "en_route",
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}"
}

###

### Submit feedback after service completion
POST {{baseUrl}}/booking/{{bookingId}}/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "userId": "<user-uuid>",
  "providerId": "{{providerId}}",
  "rating": 5,
  "reviewText": "Bahut acha kaam kiya, time pe aya!",
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}"
}

###

### Cancel/update a booking
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/booking/{{bookingId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "cancelled"
}

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### DISPUTES
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Open a dispute ticket
### Valid disputeType values: no_show | quality | price | cancellation | overrun
POST {{baseUrl}}/dispute
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookingId": "{{bookingId}}",
  "userId": "<user-uuid>",
  "providerId": "{{providerId}}",
  "disputeType": "quality",
  "description": "Provider ne AC theek nahi kiya, wahi masla baaki hai",
  "sessionId": "{{sessionId}}"
}

###

### Get a dispute by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/dispute/{{disputeId}}

###

### Get all disputes for a user
GET {{baseUrl}}/dispute/user/<user-uuid>

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### REPUTATION
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get reputation for a provider
GET {{baseUrl}}/reputation?providerId={{providerId}}

###

### Create reputation record (seed use)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reputation
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "provider_id": "{{providerId}}",
  "positive_reviews": 10,
  "negative_reviews": 1,
  "complaints": 0,
  "disputes": 0
}

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### TRACES  (agent debug logs)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### List all traces (limit 50)
GET {{baseUrl}}/traces

###

### List traces for a specific session
GET {{baseUrl}}/traces?sessionId={{sessionId}}

###
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### FEEDBACK  (direct table, bypasses reputation engine)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### List all feedback
GET {{baseUrl}}/feedback

###

### Submit feedback directly (prefer POST /booking/:id/feedback instead)
POST {{baseUrl}}/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "booking_id": "{{bookingId}}",
  "user_id": "<user-uuid>",
  "provider_id": "{{providerId}}",
  "rating": 4,
  "review_text": "Good service overall"
}

